---
import Default from '../../layouts/Default.astro';
import SectionHead from '../../components/SectionHead.astro';
import MetaStrip from '../../components/MetaStrip.astro';
---
<Default title="Demo: explore the review UI" current="notes" description="A synthetic awaiting_review candidate so you can see the review experience.">
  <div class="page-grid">
    <div class="full-bleed" style="padding: var(--space-7) var(--space-4) var(--space-3); max-width: var(--grid-max); margin: 0 auto;">
      <MetaStrip items={['NOTE', 'May 12, 2026']} />
      <h1 style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Demo: explore the review UI</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-grid">
    <div class="extended measure-tight drop-cap" style="margin-top: var(--space-5);">
      <p>
        This is a synthetic Astro draft staged at <code>tools/curator/pending_drafts/demo-review-ui.astro</code>.
        It exists so you can poke at the review modal — edit the source, save it, leave a note,
        try the reject flow — without waiting two minutes for a real pipeline pass to finish.
      </p>
      <p>
        When you're done playing, click <strong>reject</strong> with reason "demo done"
        and the candidate moves to held. Then <code>cli.sh retry demo-review-ui</code> sends it back to pending,
        or just delete the manifest at <code>~/Desktop/Fun/lab/publish_candidates/demo-review-ui.json</code>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Real drafts that arrive here will be generated by Claude from a HIVE or AGI artifact's source paths,
        scored by three MLX judges, validated by five deterministic checks, and arrive with provenance
        already injected. The only thing left for you is to read, possibly tweak, and approve.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Default>
